base_path = 'renders'

# List of image window types
window_types = ['brain_window', 'subdural_window', 'max_contrast_window', 'brain_bone_window']

# Hemorrhage categories
categories = ['subdural', 'subarachnoid', 'normal', 'multi', 'intraventricular', 'intraparenchymal', 'epidural']
In [19]:
# Structure: {category: {window_type: [list of paths]}}
images_by_window = {}

for category in categories:
    category_images = {}
    category_path = os.path.join(base_path, category, category)  # handles nested folders

    for window in window_types:
        window_path = os.path.join(category_path, window)

        if os.path.exists(window_path):
            paths = glob(os.path.join(window_path, '*.*'))
            if paths:
                category_images[window] = paths
            else:
                print(f"No images in: {window_path}")
        else:
            print(f"Window folder not found: {window_path}")
    
    if category_images:
        images_by_window[category] = category_images

# Check
if not images_by_window:
    raise ValueError("No image data found for any window.")
In [20]:
# Create 7x4 subplot: 7 categories × 4 window types
fig, ax = plt.subplots(len(categories), len(window_types), figsize=(18, 12))

for i, category in enumerate(categories):
    category_data = images_by_window.get(category, {})

    # Find filenames that exist in all 4 window types
    common_filenames = set(
        os.path.basename(p) for p in category_data.get(window_types[0], [])
    )

    for window in window_types[1:]:
        common_filenames &= set(
            os.path.basename(p) for p in category_data.get(window, [])
        )

    if not common_filenames:
        print(f"Skipping {category}: no image found in all windows.")
        for j in range(len(window_types)):
            ax[i, j].axis('off')
        continue

    # Select one image available in all windows
    chosen_filename = random.choice(list(common_filenames))

    for j, window in enumerate(window_types):
        # Find the full path for this window
        paths = category_data[window]
        img_path = next((p for p in paths if p.endswith(chosen_filename)), None)

        if img_path:
            img = cv.imread(img_path)
            if img is not None:
                ax[i, j].imshow(img, cmap='gray')
                ax[i, j].set_xticks([])
                ax[i, j].set_yticks([])
                ax[i, j].set_title(window.replace('_', ' '), fontsize=10)
                if j == 0:
                    ax[i, j].set_ylabel(category, fontsize=10)
            else:
                ax[i, j].text(0.5, 0.5, 'Load error', ha='center')
                ax[i, j].axis('off')
        else:
            ax[i, j].text(0.5, 0.5, 'Not found', ha='center')
            ax[i, j].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# -------------------------------------------
# 3. DATASET SELECTION 
# -------------------------------------------
# Load dataset WITHOUT transforms to speed up label filtering
raw_dataset = datasets.ImageFolder(root=data_dir)
class_names = raw_dataset.classes

# Select 250 image indices per class (using raw label info only)
class_to_indices = {cls: [] for cls in range(len(class_names))}
for idx, (_, label) in enumerate(raw_dataset.samples):
    if len(class_to_indices[label]) < 10000:
        class_to_indices[label].append(idx)
    if all(len(idxs) >= 1000 for idxs in class_to_indices.values()):
        break

limited_indices = [idx for indices in class_to_indices.values() for idx in indices]

# Define transforms and apply only to selected subset
transform = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize((224, 224)),
    transforms.ToTensor(),
    transforms.Normalize([0.5], [0.5])
])

full_dataset = datasets.ImageFolder(root=data_dir, transform=transform)
limited_dataset = Subset(full_dataset, limited_indices)
In [87]:
# -------------------------------------------
# 4. TRAIN/VAL SPLIT
# -------------------------------------------
train_size = int(0.8 * len(limited_dataset))
val_size = len(limited_dataset) - train_size
train_dataset, val_dataset = random_split(limited_dataset, [train_size, val_size])

train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=16, shuffle=True, num_workers=0)
val_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset, batch_size=16, num_workers=0)

# -------------------------------------------
# 5. MODEL DEFINITION
# -------------------------------------------
model = models.resnet18(pretrained=True)
model.fc = nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, len(class_names))
model = model.to(device)

criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()
optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)

# -------------------------------------------
# 6. TRAINING LOOP
# -------------------------------------------
epochs = 30
for epoch in range(epochs):
    print(f"\nStarting Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs}")
    start_time = time.time()

    model.train()
    running_loss = 0.0
    for batch_idx, (images, labels) in enumerate(tqdm(train_loader, desc=f"Training Epoch {epoch+1}")):
        images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)

        optimizer.zero_grad()
        outputs = model(images)
        loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()
        running_loss += loss.item()

    avg_train_loss = running_loss / len(train_loader)
    print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs} - Training Loss: {avg_train_loss:.4f}")

    model.eval()
    val_loss = 0.0
    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in tqdm(val_loader, desc=f"Validating Epoch {epoch+1}"):
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
            val_loss += loss.item()

    avg_val_loss = val_loss / len(val_loader)
    end_time = time.time()
    epoch_duration = end_time - start_time
    print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs} - Validation Loss: {avg_val_loss:.4f} - Time: {epoch_duration:.2f}s")

# -------------------------------------------
# 7. SAVE MODEL
# -------------------------------------------
torch.save(model.state_dict(), model_save_path)
print(f"Model saved to {model_save_path}")

# -------------------------------------------
# 8. PREDICTION SAMPLE TABLE
# -------------------------------------------
model.eval()
sample_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset, batch_size=1, shuffle=True)

rows = []
for i, (img_tensor, label) in enumerate(sample_loader):
    if i == 10:
        break
    img_tensor = img_tensor.to(device)
    with torch.no_grad():
        outputs = model(img_tensor)
        _, pred = torch.max(outputs, 1)
        predicted_class = class_names[pred.item()]
        actual_class = class_names[label.item()]
    rows.append({
        'Predicted': predicted_class,
        'Actual': actual_class
    })

results_df = pd.DataFrame(rows)
print("\nSample Predictions:")
print(results_df)

# Helper function to denormalize the image
def denormalize(tensor):
    return tensor * 0.5 + 0.5  # reverses Normalize([0.5], [0.5])

# Visualize predictions on 10 validation images
model.eval()
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 5, figsize=(16, 7))
axes = axes.flatten()

for i, (img_tensor, label) in enumerate(sample_loader):
    if i >= 10:
        break

    img_tensor = img_tensor.to(device)
    with torch.no_grad():
        output = model(img_tensor)
        _, pred = torch.max(output, 1)
        predicted_class = class_names[pred.item()]
        actual_class = class_names[label.item()]

    # Move image to CPU and denormalize
    img_np = denormalize(img_tensor.squeeze().cpu())

    # Convert to (H, W, C) if 3-channel image
    if img_np.ndim == 3:
        img_np = img_np.permute(1, 2, 0)

    axes[i].imshow(img_np, cmap='gray')
    axes[i].set_title(f"Pred: {predicted_class}\nTrue: {actual_class}")
    axes[i].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
